[ The Room is Borrowed for a Play-by-Post Call of Cthulhu Scenario ]
[ Missed Dues ]
Thursday morning. October 26. The year of our Lord 1922.
>
This is the morning like usual in Arkham, Massachusetts. The Miskatonic River flows ever gently, swaying even the toughest rocks from its slumber. The morning sky is an ever blue canvas, the sun hides under the fine sheets of fluffy clouds. People have to make their ends meet, so they flow about as well.
>
And between those people, you are there.
>
Tough and hardened faces, hands that are tainted by blood, yet the heart that yearns hope... You are all criminals of the city, leeching it off. However, bad deals lead to more bad deals. You screwed up, big time. You can surely tell that you were dying, done for, jailed forever, left down in a gutter, or some healthy mix.
>
Until, a saving grace in the form of Mordecai O'Leary came. A lieutenant of the biggest crime boss in Arkham, his influence spreads far and wide, most of them are done in less savory and even disgusting ways. But he is a man of honor, and of twisted kindness. He pulled you out from your lowest point in life, you went back on your feet, you were indebted to him a lot, and by a lot A BIG TIME, but everyone was happy.
>
Yeah, but no. Feeling indebted to an explosive man like O'Leary is never a little happy incident. He is rough and cruel. He will not hesitate to show up what his trademark nickname of "the Hammer" means. He will hammer down anyone not bowing down to him real good.
>
There's no other choice, sadly. His grips get you real tight. You need to pay O'Leary the debt you owe him back. That way at least one gruesome end for you is scratched out from the possibility.
While your character walks together to O'Leary's office, let's do some ice-breaking by introducing ourselves and just roleplay for a bit. Yeah, you guys all meet each other soon enough to save time
